Bank of America Corp DE Cuts Position in Owens-Illinois, Inc. (NYSE:OI)

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 20th, 2017 // No Comments 

Bank of America Corp DE reduced its position in shares of Owens-Illinois, Inc. (NYSE:OI) by 29.4% during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the SEC. The firm owned 1,088,231 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after selling 453,929 shares during the period. Bank of America Corp DE owned 0.67% of Owens-Illinois worth $22,178,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
Other hedge funds and other institutional investors have also recently made changes to their positions in the company. Vanguard Group Inc. boosted its position in shares of Owens-Illinois by 7.5% in the first quarter. Vanguard Group Inc. now owns 16,401,514 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $334,263,000 after buying an additional 1,139,389 shares during the period. BlackRock Inc. raised its position in shares of Owens-Illinois by 16,329.5% in the first quarter. BlackRock Inc. now owns 14,655,477 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $298,679,000 after buying an additional 14,566,275 shares during the period. Great West Life Assurance Co. Can raised its position in shares of Owens-Illinois by 0.3% in the first quarter. Great West Life Assurance Co. Can now owns 7,813,380 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $158,919,000 after buying an additional 26,764 shares during the period. Prudential Financial Inc. raised its position in shares of Owens-Illinois by 33.6% in the first quarter. Prudential Financial Inc. now owns 3,776,681 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $76,969,000 after buying an additional 949,286 shares during the period. Finally, Private Management Group Inc. raised its position in shares of Owens-Illinois by 0.4% in the first quarter. Private Management Group Inc. now owns 1,977,976 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $40,311,000 after buying an additional 8,277 shares during the period. 95.24% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 




Shares of Owens-Illinois, Inc. (NYSE OI) traded up 0.24% during mid-day trading on Wednesday, hitting $24.84. 762,279 shares of the company were exchanged. Owens-Illinois, Inc. has a 52 week low of $16.80 and a 52 week high of $25.01. The company has a 50 day moving average of $23.38 and a 200 day moving average of $21.07. The company has a market capitalization of $4.04 billion, a P/E ratio of 21.34 and a beta of 1.50. 


 Get Owens-Illinois Inc. alerts:



Owens-Illinois (NYSE:OI) last announced its quarterly earnings data on Monday, April 24th. The industrial products company reported $0.58 earnings per share for the quarter, beating analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.53 by $0.05. The company had revenue of $1.60 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $1.58 billion. Owens-Illinois had a return on equity of 80.74% and a net margin of 2.84%. The firm’s revenue for the quarter was up .8% on a year-over-year basis. During the same quarter last year, the firm posted $0.48 EPS. Equities analysts anticipate that Owens-Illinois, Inc. will post $2.50 earnings per share for the current year. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION WARNING: This report was originally published by BNB Daily and is owned by of BNB Daily. If you are viewing this report on another website, it was illegally stolen and republished in violation of US and international trademark & copyright laws. The original version of this report can be accessed at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/20/bank-of-america-corp-de-reduces-position-in-owens-illinois-inc-nyseoi-updated.html. 
Several equities analysts recently issued reports on the stock. TheStreet upgraded shares of Owens-Illinois from a “c+” rating to a “b” rating in a report on Thursday, May 4th. Citigroup Inc. dropped their target price on shares of Owens-Illinois from $28.00 to $24.00 and set an “underweight” rating on the stock in a report on Friday, April 14th. Zacks Investment Research raised shares of Owens-Illinois from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and set a $25.00 price target for the company in a research note on Monday, May 29th. Barclays PLC lifted their price target on shares of Owens-Illinois from $20.00 to $22.00 and gave the company an “equal weight” rating in a research note on Monday, May 1st. Finally, Deutsche Bank AG reaffirmed a “hold” rating and issued a $24.00 price target (up from $20.00) on shares of Owens-Illinois in a research note on Saturday, April 29th. One investment analyst has rated the stock with a sell rating, seven have given a hold rating, one has assigned a buy rating and two have issued a strong buy rating to the company. Owens-Illinois currently has a consensus rating of “Hold” and an average price target of $26.00.
Owens-Illinois Company Profile
Owens-Illinois, Inc is a manufacturer of glass container products. The Company’s principal product lines are glass containers for the food and beverage industries. The Company’s segments include Europe, North America, Latin America and Asia Pacific. The Company produces glass containers for alcoholic beverages, including beer, flavored malt beverages, spirits and wine. 

 
