Bank of America Corp DE increased its stake in  Tetra Tech, Inc. (NASDAQ:TTEK) by 33.1% during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The fund owned 218,747 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after buying an additional 54,438 shares during the period. Bank of America Corp DE owned 0.38% of Tetra Tech worth $8,936,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
