					Posted by Sally Masters on Jul 20th, 2017 // No Comments 



Bank of America Corp DE reduced its position in shares of  Valmont Industries, Inc. (NYSE:VMI) by 20.7% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The firm owned 70,500 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after selling 18,398 shares during the period. Bank of America Corp DE owned 0.31% of Valmont Industries worth $10,963,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
