										Our business practices



Print this article
Share this article












Putting responsibility into practice

Bank of America is one of the world’s leading financial institutions, serving individuals, small- and middle-market businesses, large corporations, and governments with a full range of banking, investment management and other financial and risk management products and services. Our responsible business practices have a direct, positive impact on two areas critical to our growth:

Our strength and stability as a global financial institution
Our capacity to meet the financial needs of our clients in all phases of their lives
















							Governance


Delivering responsible growth requires a strong board of directors, skilled management and clear and effective governance practices.
learn More
		 	 about Governance
















							Risk management


Managing risk well is foundational to our purpose and values – and to delivering responsible growth.
learn More
		 	 about Risk management
















							Client focus


We serve our clients through our eight lines of businesses upholding ethical standards.
learn More
		 	 about Client focus
















							Vendor management


We make sure that the goods and services we purchase in our communities come from a wide range of sources, while increasing our purchases from minority, women, veteran and other diver-owned suppliers and that suppliers have the potential to grow into long-term partners.
learn More
		 	 about Vendor management
















